  "texts": [
    "Two types of textual features extracted from the full-text of each descriptions are studied: a bag-of-word representation and word embeddings constructed using GloVe (Pennington et al., 2014).",
    "In an ablation analysis of the modalities, it was found that textual features are the most useful in the predictive model.",
    "Kaminski and Hopp (2019) experimented with several learning methods, applied to multimodal input.",
    "Textual features have been constructed using a Doc2Vec model (Le and Mikolov, 2014), which mapped the text of a document to a fixed-length vector, similar to GloVe word embeddings.",
    "Nonetheless, the distributed document representations, while being able to capture complex semantics contained in a document, cannot be used directly to explain which particular semantic properties of the documents have the greatest predictive power."
  ],
